<p class="fs-4 body-text">
    Hi! Welcome to my portfolio. 
    I'm a Senior Software Developer at RBC, where I focus on building reliable, maintainable software that solves real business problems. 
    My current work centers around enterprise Python development, automation, and modernizing legacy systems, with a strong focus on software quality, long-term maintainability, and continuous improvement.
<br/><br/>
    My passion for software development started in high school, where I was first introduced to programming through an introductory course. 
    I was immediately hooked, and knew early on that this was the career I wanted to pursue.
<br/><br/>
    My path into software wasn't a straight one. 
    Due to personal circumstances, I spent five years working as a repair technician at Lenovo's repair depot. 
    My time there taught me how to approach problems methodically, troubleshoot under pressure, and focus on finding root causes instead of quick fixes. 
    These are skills I still rely on every day as a software developer.
<br/><br/>
    Around the time of the pandemic, I decided it was time to fully pursue my passion for software development. 
    I enrolled at Canadore College, completed my diploma with honours, and began my first professional role as a software developer.
<br/><br/>
    Not long after, I was given the opportunity to continue my education abroad and moved to Ireland to complete my degree at South East Technological University in Carlow. 
    My time at SETU was one of the most formative experiences of my career, where I was exposed to many of the concepts that now define how I approach software development, including clean architecture, SOLID principles, Test Driven Development, secure development, and thoughtful software design.
<br/><br/>
    After completing my degree, I moved back to Canada and joined RBC, where I've continued to grow as an engineer while putting those lessons into practice. 
    My work has included building enterprise automation solutions, modernizing legacy processes, supporting production systems, and helping improve software quality across multiple codebases.
</p>
